cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Forward-Registered, Auditable LLM-Assisted Research: A Reliability Methodology, with a Capital-Markets Testbed"
message: "If you use this framework, please cite it."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Zheng
    given-names: Yixing
    email: yz11739@stern.nyu.edu
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0009-0000-0563-2398"
repository-code: "https://github.com/yixingz3/qpop"
abstract: >-
  Methods for making AI- and LLM-assisted research reliable, auditable, and
  reproducible. The framework wraps open-ended agentic discovery in deterministic,
  independently-auditable gates and a forward pre-registration ("forward-QPOP")
  protocol, so that each accept/reject decision is verifiable rather than a black-box
  narrative and is evaluated forward rather than by a leakage-prone backtest. It is
  validated on high-stakes capital-markets and economic forecasting as an adversarial
  testbed, and is domain-agnostic by construction. Components include a portable
  bottleneck graph, a decomposed confidence model, a budget-aware cheap-source /
  deterministic-gate / expensive-evaluate funnel, a tamper-evident hypothesis ledger,
  and a held-out rejection-quality audit.
keywords:
  - large language models
  - LLM agents
  - AI reliability
  - auditable AI
  - trustworthy AI
  - pre-registration
  - forward validation
  - over-admission rate
  - reproducibility
  - backtest overfitting
  - look-ahead bias
  - machine learning in finance
license: MIT
